Business Brief -- Tenneco Inc.:
   Pulp Chemicals Operation
   To Be Sold for $202 Million
Sterling Chemicals is a petrochemical concern based in
Houston.
   Michael H. Walsh, Tenneco president and chief executive
officer, said the company intends to "proceed with the sale
of other non-core assets" and other strategies to strengthen
the balance sheet. Tenneco is in the middle of a plan to cut
9,000 jobs by the end of 1992, reducing world-wide employment
to slightly below 90,000 in 33 countries.
   Tenneco said that in the fourth quarter, its overall
chemical business wasn't profitable. The company doesn't
elaborate on details of that segment.